item.title: Just saying .....
item.description: As for the hand-wringing and pearl-clutching over Mamdani's win. Democratic socialism has been part of our country for over a century, and you've enjoyed many of the benefits. Roads, firefighters, public defenders, public hospitals, public schools, etc, and so on. Most of Europe is run by governments with some form of socialism. The happiest and safest countries in the world are run by some form of socialism - Sweden, Norway, and Finland all come to mind. What you don't want is a fascist socialist government - and that one word matters. Fascism fucks over all forms of government. Democratic socialism seems to work better (for the average person) than most forms of government as long as the checks and balances stay in place and are heeded (you know - the very things Trump is just ignoring?). New York is one of the wealthiest states in the nation - it'll subsidize itself during this experiment, unlike all the red states that keep doubling down on capitalism even when it means they have to use socialism (handouts from the federal taxes paid by blue states) to save their backsides. Also, most of you don't even LIVE in New York. Any socialist shifts will only impact you IF THEY WORK, and other states want to follow suit.

item.title: GovBrief Today #279
item.description: Our biggest challenge is to bear witness to the suffering around us. World Central Kitchen is feeding unpaid government workers in DC as they might people in a war zone or disaster area. The government's partial funding for SNAP this month means that five million Americans who are food insecure will receive nothing. Judges are ordering the government to comply with the law. One restored ASL signers to the White House after Trump disenfranchised hearing impaired people. Another ordered changes at an ICE facility in suburban Chicago where people were crowded 100+ to a cell and forced to sleep on top of each other and next to open toilets. We're openly calling our government authoritarian now, but we can't be numb to this suffering. Let's help those in our communities who need food or shelter now. Let's also call Democratic representatives and tell them to hold fast. Yesterday's election results show that people are understanding the emergency. Let's not cave on insurance subsidies and create a healthcare crisis on top of everything else. Notice you're seeing less news on social media? We track the data - you're right.
